WEBVTT

00:04.838 --> 00:05.806 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Good evening.

00:05.839 --> 00:06.807 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm Judy Woodruff.

00:06.840 --> 00:08.709 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: And I'm Gwen Ifill.

00:08.742 --> 00:11.545 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: We bring you the
"NewsHour"
tonight from the Wells Fargo
Center in Philadelphia,

00:11.578 --> 00:14.448 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
site of this week's Democratic
National Convention.

00:14.481 --> 00:19.353 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
GWEN IFILL: It's the
convention's final day,
the climax of a week of
friction, politics

00:19.386 --> 00:26.126 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and excitement, as Democrats
prepare to hear
tonight from their nominee,
Hillary Clinton.

00:26.159 --> 00:31.198 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Plus: as the
glass ceiling
shatters, a look at the ways
hidden sexism

00:31.231 --> 00:34.501 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
is playing out this election
among some male
voters.

00:34.534 --> 00:40.240 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DANIEL BUSH: Benevolent sexism,
which, from
a male point of view, encourages
men to be

00:40.274 --> 00:44.378 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
supportive of women who are in
traditional
roles, traditional gender roles,
but when

00:44.411 --> 00:47.347 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
women step out of that, men tend
to look at
them worse.

00:47.381 --> 00:49.449 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: And I'm Hari
Sreenivasan
in Washington.

00:49.483 --> 00:54.087 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
We will have all the
non-convention news of
the days, a shocking update on
what began

00:54.121 --> 00:57.991 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
as an economic Cinderella story
in a depressed
corner of Vermont.

00:58.025 --> 01:01.962 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Job growth funded by a green
card program
ends in large-scale fraud.

01:01.995 --> 01:08.802 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: All that and more on
tonight's
"PBS NewsHour."

01:08.835 --> 01:10.904 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

01:10.938 --> 01:22.783 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: It's the night the
Democrats have
been building toward all week.

01:22.816 --> 01:28.088 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In just a few hours, Hillary
Clinton takes
center stage, picking up the
baton handed

01:28.121 --> 01:31.692 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to her last night by President
Obama.

01:31.725 --> 01:33.994 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Correspondent John Yang begins
our coverage.

01:34.027 --> 01:39.232 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Inside the Wells
Fargo Center in
Philadelphia, the stage is set
for tonight's

01:39.266 --> 01:43.337 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
big moment, Hillary Clinton's
acceptance speech.

01:43.370 --> 01:47.441 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Campaign officials say she will
highlight
the gathering's theme: stronger
together.

01:47.474 --> 01:50.744 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JENNIFER PALMIERI, Clinton
Campaign Communications
Director: This is a moment of
reckoning for

01:50.777 --> 01:55.749 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
America, and we have two paths
that we can
take, one that seeks division,
one that gives

01:55.782 --> 02:01.888 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
into forces that we are facing,
whether they
are economic or social, that
could divide

02:01.922 --> 02:07.661 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
us, vs. a path that, in working
together,
is going to make America
stronger.

02:07.694 --> 02:11.999 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Even though Clinton's
been in the
public eye for more than two
decades, her

02:12.032 --> 02:16.236 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
campaign considers this her
introduction to
the American people.

02:16.269 --> 02:19.606 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They call her the most famous
unknown person
in America.

02:19.639 --> 02:25.178 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
She will be preceded on the
stage by her daughter,
Chelsea.

02:25.212 --> 02:31.518 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It won't be the nominee's first
time on the
convention stage this week.

02:31.551 --> 02:36.957 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Last night, she made a surprise
appearance
after President Obama's rousing
45-minute

02:36.990 --> 02:38.759 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
endorsement.

02:38.792 --> 02:40.527 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BARACK OBAMA, President of the
United States:
That's why I can say with
confidence there

02:40.560 --> 02:49.136 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
has never been a man or a woman,
not me, not
Bill, nobody, more qualified
than Hillary

02:49.169 --> 02:51.038 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Clinton to serve as president of
the United
States of America.

02:51.071 --> 02:52.773 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
(CHEERING AND APPLAUSE)

02:52.806 --> 02:58.545 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BARACK OBAMA: I hope you don't
mind, Bill,
but I was just telling the
truth, man.

02:58.578 --> 03:04.351 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Today, Clinton's
running mate,
Virginia Senator Tim Kaine,
spoke to delegates

03:04.384 --> 03:06.253 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
from his childhood home of
Missouri.

03:06.286 --> 03:07.854 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

03:07.888 --> 03:09.256 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
TIM KAINE (D-VA), Vice
Presidential Candidate:
We have a chance to make
history.

03:09.289 --> 03:11.825 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And when Hillary Clinton is
elected, that's
going to be historic.

03:11.858 --> 03:16.263 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But what's really going to be
historic is,
it's going to open up the
possibly of a whole

03:16.296 --> 03:21.468 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
different class of successors,
just like when
President Obama was elected.

03:21.501 --> 03:26.239 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Meanwhile, Republican
Donald Trump
continues to campaign, holding
rallies in

03:26.273 --> 03:28.041 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Iowa.

03:28.075 --> 03:32.312 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Earlier, in a FOX News
interview, he was in
damage control, after he
suggested yesterday

03:32.345 --> 03:37.250 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
that Russia find tens of
thousands of e-mails
missing from Clinton's private
server.

03:37.284 --> 03:39.686 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP (R), Presidential
Candidate:
When I'm being sarcastic with
something.

03:39.719 --> 03:41.154 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
QUESTION: Were you being
sarcastic?

03:41.188 --> 03:42.155 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP: Of course I'm
being sarcastic.

03:42.189 --> 03:45.158 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But you have 33,000 e-mails
deleted.

03:45.192 --> 03:49.296 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And the real problem is what was
said on those
e-mails from the Democratic
National Committee.

03:49.329 --> 03:52.299 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You take a look at what was said
on those
e-mails, it's disgraceful.

03:52.332 --> 03:58.004 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: In Philadelphia, as
the convention
reaches its climax, police
remain on alert.

03:58.038 --> 04:01.842 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Protests have been mostly
peaceful, with only
a small number of arrests.

04:01.875 --> 04:05.445 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," I'm John
Yang in Philadelphia.

04:05.479 --> 04:10.984 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: One thing that
has been clear
this week in Philadelphia is
that this has

04:11.017 --> 04:13.720 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
been a week of criticism of
Donald Trump.

04:13.753 --> 04:15.522 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Let's take a look at that.

04:15.555 --> 04:21.394 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MICHELLE OBAMA, First Lady:
Don't let anyone
ever tell you that this country
isn't great,

04:21.428 --> 04:28.201 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that somehow we need to make it
great again,
because this, right now, is the
greatest country

04:28.235 --> 04:29.202 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
on Earth.

04:29.236 --> 04:31.037 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

04:31.071 --> 04:33.773 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
BERNIE SANDERS (VT-I),
Presidential Candidate:
If you don't believe that this
election is

04:33.807 --> 04:41.882 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
important, if you think you can
sit it out,
take a moment to think about the
Supreme Court

04:41.915 --> 04:44.317 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
justices that Donald Trump would
nominate.

04:44.351 --> 04:49.189 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MICHAEL BLOOMBERG (I), Former
Mayor of New
York: Bottom line is, Trump is a
risky, reckless

04:49.222 --> 04:52.626 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and radical choice, and we can't
afford to
make that choice.

04:52.659 --> 04:54.327 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

04:54.361 --> 05:00.667 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TIM KAINE: Folks, you cannot
believe one word
that comes out of Donald Trump's
mouth.

05:00.700 --> 05:04.971 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOSEPH BIDEN, Vice President of
the United
States: His cynicism is
unbounded.

05:05.005 --> 05:10.844 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
His lack of empathy and
compassion can be
summed up in the phrase I
suspect he's most

05:10.877 --> 05:14.347 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
proud of having made famous,
"You're fired."

05:14.381 --> 05:19.186 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
How can there be pleasure in
saying, "You're
fired"?

05:19.219 --> 05:24.257 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He is trying to tell us he cares
about the
middle class?

05:24.291 --> 05:25.692 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Give me a break.

05:25.725 --> 05:27.494 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
That's a bunch of malarkey.

05:27.527 --> 05:32.432 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BARACK OBAMA: Our power doesn't
come from
some self-declared savior
promising that he

05:32.465 --> 05:36.803 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
alone can restore order as long
as we do things
his way.

05:36.836 --> 05:38.672 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We don't look to be ruled.

05:38.705 --> 05:41.474 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
(CHEERING AND APPLAUSE)

05:41.508 --> 05:50.884 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BARACK OBAMA: Our power -- our
power comes
from those immortal declarations
first put

05:50.917 --> 05:56.590 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
to paper right here in
Philadelphia all those
years ago: We hold these truths
to be self-evident,

05:56.623 --> 06:04.231 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that all men are created equal,
that we the
people can form a more perfect
union.

06:04.264 --> 06:10.637 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: And now we turn to
Hillary Clinton's
strategist and pollster Joel
Benenson.

06:10.670 --> 06:12.505 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And Joel joins us now.

06:12.539 --> 06:16.843 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Tell us about that -- now that
this campaign,
this convention is almost over,
as you launch

06:16.876 --> 06:20.513 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
into the general election, tell
us what the
key expectations are.

06:20.547 --> 06:22.015 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOEL BENENSON, Clinton Campaign
Adviser: For
tonight or going forward?

06:22.048 --> 06:23.550 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Going forward.

06:23.583 --> 06:25.785 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOEL BENENSON: Look, I think
that we're in
the homestretch here, really.

06:25.819 --> 06:28.221 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
You have about 100 days to go.

06:28.255 --> 06:33.760 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The convention is the last time
you get four
days to deliver your message
unfiltered without

06:33.793 --> 06:38.698 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
interference largely from your
opponent, although
Trump kind of tried a little bit
yesterday.

06:38.732 --> 06:40.033 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Interference.

06:40.066 --> 06:41.935 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOEL BENENSON: I think he
created for interference
for himself.

06:41.968 --> 06:44.871 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think what you want going
forward is, tonight,
you are going to see Hillary
Clinton lay out

06:44.904 --> 06:49.643 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a very clear choice of two
visions for America,
one that is optimistic, one that
is rooted

06:49.676 --> 06:53.813 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in the beliefs that we have
always been stronger
together as a country, from the
time our founders

06:53.847 --> 06:58.218 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
struggled to come together in
Philadelphia,
in this city, to create this
nation up and

06:58.251 --> 07:00.020 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
through today.

07:00.053 --> 07:03.123 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And with the challenges we face,
that's how
we will live up to our values
and be at our

07:03.156 --> 07:08.995 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
best, vs. a very dark divisive
-- divisive
vision that Donald Trump laid
out.

07:09.029 --> 07:10.764 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I think you have got to
drive that every
day.

07:10.797 --> 07:13.266 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think you have got to talk
about how you're
going to create an economy that
works for

07:13.300 --> 07:18.271 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
everyone, not just those at the
top, draw
a clear contrast on who can keep
America safe.

07:18.305 --> 07:23.443 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think Mr. Trump, Donald Trump,
proved this
week he can't do that with
erratic statements,

07:23.476 --> 07:26.913 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
like inviting Russia to start
hacking computers.

07:26.946 --> 07:28.715 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And I think you drive that every
day.

07:28.748 --> 07:31.951 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That's what you have to do that
from here
on out, consistently show people
the differences

07:31.985 --> 07:35.689 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
about where you are going to
take the country,
what your values are that are
driving you

07:35.722 --> 07:37.557 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and will shape your presidency.

07:37.590 --> 07:41.061 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, Joel
Benenson, are you
describing an effort to be just
about as negative

07:41.094 --> 07:43.897 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
toward Donald Trump as the
Republicans are
toward Hillary Clinton?

07:43.930 --> 07:45.765 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JOEL BENENSON: No.

07:45.799 --> 07:47.867 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think what I said is, you have
got to lay
out a choice and you have got to
do some contrast.

07:47.901 --> 07:49.803 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
They're doing only contrast.

07:49.836 --> 07:54.074 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Donald Trump, as you heard
President Obama
say last night, has one answer:
I alone can

07:54.107 --> 07:55.875 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
fix it.

07:55.909 --> 07:59.346 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He has got no prescriptions, no
real plans
that will create a single job,
no real plans

07:59.379 --> 08:02.148 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that will raise wages in America
or educate
a single child.

08:02.182 --> 08:06.853 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What Hillary Clinton has to do,
on balance,
is show people the positive,
affirmative,

08:06.886 --> 08:12.325 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
uplifting vision she has, her
belief in the
way we solve our problems is by
working together,

08:12.359 --> 08:16.496 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
by having each other's backs,
lifting each
other up, not tearing each other
apart.

08:16.529 --> 08:21.468 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think you lean very heavily
towards the
positive, but you have to call
out your differences,

08:21.501 --> 08:25.739 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
particularly when you have got
someone, as
you're hearing at this
convention, whom even

08:25.772 --> 08:30.443 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Democrats are calling a
demagogue, who are
turning away from their party,
who say -- people

08:30.477 --> 08:32.278 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
like Michael Bloomberg.

08:32.312 --> 08:34.714 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Tonight, you will hear from
another one saying
it's -- we have to put our
country ahead of

08:34.748 --> 08:35.715 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
our party.

08:35.749 --> 08:37.550 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: But here's the
thing.

08:37.584 --> 08:42.455 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You're banking on the idea that
talking about
the positive and personalizing
this toward

08:42.489 --> 08:48.328 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Donald Trump will somehow
outbalance this
nervousness among a lot of
individual Americans

08:48.361 --> 08:50.663 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that you're not listening, that
their lives
are not doing so well.

08:50.697 --> 08:52.665 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOEL BENENSON: Oh, I don't think
I said that
at all, Gwen.

08:52.699 --> 08:56.436 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think, in fact, what I said
is, you have
to have an affirmative vision of
how you're

08:56.469 --> 08:59.639 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
going to create an economy that
works for
everyone.

08:59.672 --> 09:01.608 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That's not being personal about
Donald Trump.

09:01.641 --> 09:06.079 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
When Donald Trump says to
Americans, wages
are too high, you're not going
to create an

09:06.112 --> 09:08.148 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
economy that works for everyone
when you believe
that.

09:08.181 --> 09:10.850 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You have to do things that are
going to help
people get ahead in their lives.

09:10.884 --> 09:15.255 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And the bulk of what we have
been talking
about throughout our primaries
is how to put

09:15.288 --> 09:17.390 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the plans in place to do that.

09:17.424 --> 09:21.528 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
One thing that Hillary Clinton
will be doing
in part in this speech and going
forward is

09:21.561 --> 09:23.463 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
laying out very specific plans.

09:23.496 --> 09:27.901 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
She said in one of the speeches
she gave a
couple of weeks ago, I have got
this old-fashioned

09:27.934 --> 09:29.702 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
idea.

09:29.736 --> 09:32.105 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
When you're running for
president, you have
got to tell people what you're
going to do,

09:32.138 --> 09:34.340 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
how you're going to get it done
