right-to-work, they
come back across the bridge.

41:55.213 --> 41:58.649 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Look, in the last election, we
had the same
problem with Barack Obama.

41:58.683 --> 42:03.321 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It was because of race, not sex
at that point
or gender.

42:03.354 --> 42:08.359 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And we were able, given our
program, talking
our member-to-member program, it
was a 56-percent

42:08.393 --> 42:14.465 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
difference, 56-point difference
between union
white males and the white males
of the general

42:14.499 --> 42:18.970 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
population, because we gave them
the facts,
we talked to them,
member-to-member stuff,

42:19.003 --> 42:21.406 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and we will be able to do the
same thing in
this election.

42:21.439 --> 42:25.510 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Senator Booker,
given what we
know about Donald Trump's
strengths, as well

42:25.543 --> 42:30.348 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
as Hillary Clinton's strengths
and weaknesses,
who are the Clinton voters and
who are not

42:30.381 --> 42:31.349 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the Clinton voters?

42:31.382 --> 42:32.350 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Who's not worth going after?

42:32.383 --> 42:34.152 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

42:34.185 --> 42:34.852 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CORY BOOKER (D), New Jersey:
Well, I think
we have got to play the full
court and try

42:34.886 --> 42:36.087 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to get every voter that we can.

42:36.120 --> 42:38.222 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Now, there's naturally a base
for the Democratic
Party.

42:38.256 --> 42:43.060 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And any Democrat running is
trying to get
that Obama coalition, which is
an increasingly

42:43.094 --> 42:44.462 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
diverse voter base.

42:44.495 --> 42:45.463 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It's young folks.

42:45.496 --> 42:48.166 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's minorities, as well as
white women.

42:48.199 --> 42:53.738 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But I don't think we as a party
can afford
to alienate or not try to speak
to the concerns,

42:53.771 --> 42:56.674 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
fears, insecurities, aspirations
of white
men.

42:56.707 --> 42:58.109 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We should not give up that
ground.

42:58.142 --> 42:59.110 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: How do you do that?

42:59.143 --> 43:00.111 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
How does she do that?

43:00.144 --> 43:02.013 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

43:02.046 --> 43:04.048 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CORY BOOKER: Well, I think we do
that by talking
about the issues, by talking
about where people

43:04.081 --> 43:07.552 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
are, what they're struggling
with, whether
it's the high cost of college
education, whether

43:07.585 --> 43:11.789 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
it's the fact that they're
working harder
than their parents, but making
less money.

43:11.823 --> 43:16.627 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's trying to do things like
talk to them
about expanding opportunity
through infrastructure

43:16.661 --> 43:19.697 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
investment and the kind of
things that grow
solid middle-class jobs.

43:19.730 --> 43:21.499 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
So, I'm a competitor.

43:21.532 --> 43:24.268 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I don't want to say, hey,
just because
this person is a woman or this
person is a

43:24.302 --> 43:26.137 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
minority, that they're not going
to get the
white male vote.

43:26.170 --> 43:29.073 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We want everybody to think about
what's in
their interests.

43:29.106 --> 43:34.278 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I believe that our party
platform has
a better vision and better
actually pathway

43:34.312 --> 43:38.483 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
for white Americans, as well
black Americans,
Latino Americans, women, and so
forth, to

43:38.516 --> 43:40.218 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
be successful.

43:40.251 --> 43:43.488 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: But, Rich Trumka,
how do you
know that describing what
Hillary Clinton

43:43.521 --> 43:49.093 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
