we try to organize
a work site.

44:11.148 --> 44:16.554 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We're able to get through that
by talking
through the facts and having
people join together.

44:16.587 --> 44:19.390 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Look, Donald Trump, I will say
three things
about Donald Trump.

44:19.423 --> 44:21.058 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
One, he's unfit to be president.

44:21.092 --> 44:26.063 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Two, he would make it much more
difficult
for working people to make ends
meet.

44:26.097 --> 44:28.232 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And, three, he would tear our
country apart.

44:28.266 --> 44:32.203 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
When you talk to them about
those three things,
they really do understand.

44:32.236 --> 44:33.938 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
They're very thoughtful.

44:33.971 --> 44:35.606 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Working people really amaze me.

44:35.640 --> 44:39.744 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
When you give them all the
facts, they make
the right decision every single
time.

44:39.777 --> 44:43.481 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: But given what we
have seen here
on this convention floor, isn't
trade policy,

44:43.514 --> 44:46.317 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
couldn't that be a breaking
point, a weak
point?

44:46.350 --> 44:49.053 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
RICHARD TRUMKA: Well, it's an
exceptional
-- it's exceptionally important.

44:49.086 --> 44:51.155 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Look, we have a raising wages
agenda.

44:51.188 --> 44:53.925 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And that includes tax policy,
trade policy.

44:53.958 --> 44:55.860 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
TPP is a very bad agreement.

44:55.893 --> 45:00.264 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Covers 40 percent of the world's
economy,
and it will cost us jobs.

45:00.298 --> 45:02.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It's not well-drafted.

45:02.066 --> 45:07.471 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's an agreement, an investment
agreement
that will benefit Wall Street a
lot, but not

45:07.505 --> 45:08.606 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
working people.

45:08.639 --> 45:11.075 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Hillary Clinton has the same
exact position.

45:11.108 --> 45:12.810 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
She's against TPP.

45:12.843 --> 45:14.045 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
She will be against TPP.

45:14.078 --> 45:15.279 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
GWEN IFILL: Now.

45:15.313 --> 45:16.981 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
That's all it takes?

45:17.014 --> 45:21.953 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RICHARD TRUMKA: Well, but, look,
let's talk
about what's a responsible
legislator.

45:21.986 --> 45:26.123 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You can be dogmatic, like Donald
Trump, and
say don't tell me any of the
facts, I have

45:26.157 --> 45:30.928 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
made up my mind, I don't want to
hear anything,
or you can say, look, trade can
be good or

45:30.962 --> 45:34.165 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
it can be bad, depending on the
rules.

45:34.198 --> 45:38.836 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
When she saw the rules that were
drafted,
she said, this doesn't make it,
just like

45:38.869 --> 45:39.837 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
we did.

45:39.870 --> 45:41.305 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And so she was against it.

45:41.339 --> 45:43.741 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
That's responsible legislating.

45:43.774 --> 45:46.844 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I wish more legislators would do
exactly that.

45:46.877 --> 45:51.115 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Senator Booker,
pick up on
that, because we have got a
chorus of Bernie

45:51.148 --> 45:55.720 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Sanders supporters out there
who, for the
last three nights, have been
holding up signs

45:55.753 --> 46:00.725 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
-- or, essentially, their
argument is, Hillary
Clinton was late to this
position, she took

46:00.758 --> 46:02.293 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
this position for political
reasons.

46:02.326 --> 46:04.161 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
