still exists
among men?

49:10.247 --> 49:17.087 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RICHARD TRUMKA: We started --
after Ferguson,
I appointed a race commission in
the AFL-CIO.

49:17.121 --> 49:23.060 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And we went around the country
talking first
to our members, outside the
spotlight, not

49:23.093 --> 49:25.663 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
public conversations, but
private conversations.

49:25.696 --> 49:28.799 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And it was amazing to see the
difference.

49:28.833 --> 49:33.971 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
It takes about an
hour-and-a-half for people
in a room to start trusting each
other enough

49:34.004 --> 49:38.175 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to be able to start telling
what's really
in their heart and then sharing
it with one

49:38.209 --> 49:39.176 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
another.

49:39.210 --> 49:40.678 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They don't feel they are going
to be attacked.

49:40.711 --> 49:46.183 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The same is true about sex
gender.

49:46.217 --> 49:52.756 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Look, we had this conversation
when Hillary
ran against President Obama.

49:52.790 --> 49:54.625 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We had that conversation.

49:54.658 --> 49:57.728 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We had a twofer at that time,
because I would
say to our members, if you're
not voting for

49:57.761 --> 50:00.998 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Barack Obama because he's black,
you're wrong.

50:01.031 --> 50:05.569 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If you're not voting for Hillary
Clinton because
she's a woman, you're equally
wrong.

50:05.603 --> 50:07.738 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And so we started that
conversation.

50:07.771 --> 50:09.607 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We still have a long way to go.

50:09.640 --> 50:14.144 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think, quite frankly, we're
further along
with that conversation with the
American worker

50:14.178 --> 50:15.980 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
than we are with race.

50:16.013 --> 50:20.417 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think race is sort of more
hidden and more
difficult to pull out and get
people to start

50:20.451 --> 50:21.418 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
confronting and talking about.

50:21.452 --> 50:23.254 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

50:23.287 --> 50:25.422 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CORY BOOKER: But I see great
signs, when you
have the head of the FBI,
Republican, Comey,

50:25.456 --> 50:28.392 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
